Done (technical baseline):
  ✔ Google Search Console: property verified for https://gotrippin.app @done(26-04-03)
  ✔ Preferred landing URL: / → /home; sitemap lists canonical URLs only @done(26-04-03)
  ✔ Canonical consistency: root layout vs per-route; no mixed signals with redirects @done(26-04-03)
  ✔ NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL: production https://gotrippin.app (no www) — env must match live host; never commit .env @done(26-04-03 stakeholder)
  ✔ Landing: one H1; logical heading hierarchy @done(26-04-03)

Phase 1 — Homepage IA & narrative (primary SEO work):
  ✔ Map sections (story → map → AI → together + bento + final CTA); arturia + tripsy refs @done(26-04-03)
  ✔ Hero visuals: wireframe placeholders in /public/landing (swap WebP when ready — README) @done(26-04-03)
  ✔ CTA microcopy: “plan”; footer + bento aligned @done(26-04-03)
  ✔ Keyword map: intent → on-page placement (EN) — ref `docs/seo/marketing/seo-search-intent-trip-planning-2026-04.md` @done(26-04-03)
      Map (section id → intent phrases): `#story` group trip chaos / scattered plans; `#map` shared route, map, itinerary shape; `#ai` trip planning assistant, itinerary help; `#together` shared plan, one link, group; `#apps` web-first, native planned; `#trust` early access, feedback; `#sheets` spreadsheet alternative; `#features` bento (map + AI + share); `#faq` objections; hero H1 group trip + shared itinerary; metadata title/description align with same phrases (no stuffing).
  ✔ Landing body copy: truthful sharing roadmap @done(26-04-03)
  ☐ Locale strategy: single URL + i18n cookie — document crawler tradeoff; BG URLs when ready

Phase 2 — Meta, rich results, social:
  ✔ Title + meta description: /home updated; no “route-first” @done(26-04-03)
  ✔ JSON-LD: `WebApplication` + on-page `FAQPage` on `/home` (EN/BG copy via cookie lang for HTML + schema) @done(26-04-03)
  ✔ Open Graph: `app/home/opengraph-image.tsx` (1200×630); `twitter:card` summary_large_image on `/home` metadata @done(26-04-03)

Phase 3 — Trust & crawl hygiene:
  ✔ /privacy and /terms stub routes linked from footer (robots: noindex until real copy) @done(26-04-03)
  ☐ robots.ts: revisit disallow when new public routes ship
  ☐ Crawlable content: key marketing text in initial HTML; spot-check rendered source

Phase 4 — Performance spot-check (non-blocking):
  ☐ Core Web Vitals / PSI mobile — re-run after homepage work stabilizes

Phase 5 — International (when ready):
  ☐ Hreflang: real locale URLs + reciprocal + x-default
  ☐ Until then: one crawler-facing language; skip hreflang

Phase 6 — After launch / distribution:
  ☐ Backlinks: ethical listings, roundups, founder content
  ☐ Monthly GSC: queries, CTR, coverage — once homepage is indexed

Phase 6b — App Store / Play (when native app ships):
  ☐ ASO baseline per `docs/seo/marketing/aso-vs-web-seo-trip-planning-2026-04.md` (title, subtitle/short desc, keywords iOS, long description Android, screenshots, category, honest copy per Play policy)
  ☐ Align store listing value prop with `/home` (no contradictory claims)

Phase 7 — Google: submit last (when the page is ready to represent the product):
  ☐ GSC → Sitemaps: submit https://gotrippin.app/sitemap.xml
  ☐ GSC URL Inspection: /home and / — confirm Google-selected canonical matches intent
  ☐ Re-test in GSC after major URL or canonical changes

Notes:
  Bing Webmaster Tools: dropped from this checklist (optional ad-hoc if you want).
  Competitive head terms take months; prioritize brand, long-tail, locale queries.
  Risky mistakes: contradictory canonicals, thin pages at scale, blocking important URLs.
  Hero / tagline notes: docs/seo/marketing/hero-tagline-research.md
